dct_description_sm: Relief shown by shading and spot heights. Map shows four classes of roads (metalled, motor, dry, and cycles), two classes of railways (existing and planned), international, intercolonial, provincial, and district boundaries, telegraphs, principle towns and administrative centres, administrative centres, stations and settlements, missions, the principle remains of forts, and relief by shading and spot heights. Original map is filed in the Map and Geospatial Information Center. A map reproduction is attached to companion volume.
